"#feedbackModal_main_3616704\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wfn1665703029011.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wfn1665703029011.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wfn1665703029011.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wfn1665703029011\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Window Properties\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This property defines an associative list of properties that control the appearance and behavior of a form component running in a Windows environment.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__p_d99869e1_d99870e1_d99871e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">$windowproperties(\"FORM2\", \"backimage\") = \"backimage=@%%LOGO.MYENT%%%.png\")</code>\n</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__table_d11606e1_d11607e1_d11608e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Expected Value:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">String</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Default Value:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">None</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__section_j4t_hhl_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d292795e100\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__p_d99875e1_d99876e1_d99877e1\">The window properties are the widget properties of a\n            form component. Selected properties can be set in ProcScript using\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">newinstance</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$windowproperties</span>. For more\n            information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ryt1665702577808.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ryt1665702577808.html\" title=\"Creates a new instance of a component.\">newinstance</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bch1665702773514.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bch1665702773514.html\" title=\"Set or return the current window properties of a Form instance.\">$windowproperties</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__section_kjb_jhl_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d292795e129\">Window Properties</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__p_d99881e1_d99882e1_d99883e1\">The following window properties can be set\n            declaratively in <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Properties</span>, and dynamically with the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$widgetproperties</span> ProcScript function.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__ul_s1p_khl_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40358e1_d40359e1_d40360e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rwc1665702587483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rwc1665702587483.html\" title=\"Color to use as the background of the object.\">Background Color (BackColor)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40361e1_d40362e1_d40363e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rbp1665702587714.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rbp1665702587714.html\" title=\"Color to use as the foreground (usually the text color).\">Foreground Color (ForeColor)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40364e1_d40365e1_d40366e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"scc1665702611448.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/scc1665702611448.html\" title=\"Image used as background for the application window, form, or entity. This property can be set in ProcScript.\">Background Image (BackImage)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40367e1_d40368e1_d40369e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kmv1665702611521.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kmv1665702611521.html\" title=\"This property determines how the data (text or image) is aligned in the widget, entity, area frame, or window.\">Horizontal Alignment (Halign)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40370e1_d40371e1_d40372e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gvp1665702611605.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gvp1665702611605.html\" title=\"This property determines the vertical alignment of data (text or image) in the widget, entity, area frame, or window.\">Vertical Alignment ( Valign)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40373e1_d40374e1_d40375e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dbd1665702611680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dbd1665702611680.html\" title=\"This property determines how the image is horizontally scaled; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent).\">Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40376e1_d40377e1_d40378e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sup1665702611757.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sup1665702611757.html\" title=\"This property determines how the image is scaled vertically; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent).\">Vertical Scaling ( Vscale)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40379e1_d40380e1_d40381e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yxe1665702611833.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yxe1665702611833.html\" title=\"Determines whether the aspect ratio of the image is preserved at all times. True (default) or False.\">Preserve Aspect Ratio ( PreserveAspect)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__p_d99884e1_d99885e1_d99886e1\">The following window properties can be set\n            declaratively in <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Properties</span>, and in ProcScript with\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">newinstance</span>.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__ul_hbp_khl_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40382e1_d40383e1_d40384e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dto1665702580637.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dto1665702580637.html\" title=\"Window property of a form that determines the type of window used to display the form. One of: Normal | Dialog | Primary | Secondary | Contained | Popup\">Window Type (WindowType)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40385e1_d40386e1_d40387e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yte1665702580476.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yte1665702580476.html\" title=\"Determines whether the form instance can lose focus without being closed. Valid values are Modal or Non-Modal (instance can lose and get focus)\">Modality</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40388e1_d40389e1_d40390e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rld1665702581999.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rld1665702581999.html\" title=\"Window property of a form that determines what happens when it loses input focus. It may be automatically closed and the Quit or Accept trigger fired , or it may stay open and be explicitly closed. Valid values: Quit or True, Accept , or False.\">Auto Close (AutoClose)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__p_d99887e1_d99888e1_d99889e1\">The following properties can be set declaratively in\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Window Properties</span>, but not in ProcScript:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__ul_mbp_khl_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40391e1_d40392e1_d40393e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kno1665702715076.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kno1665702715076.html\" title=\"Window property that determines whether the form window has a title bar. Valid values: True (default) or False.\">Caption</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40394e1_d40395e1_d40396e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ecw1665702715443.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ecw1665702715443.html\" title=\"Window property of a form or application shell that determines whether the Windows system menu and buttons to minimize, maximize, and close the window are available for this window. Valid values: True or False.\">System Menu (SysMenu)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40397e1_d40398e1_d40399e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cwr1665702715216.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cwr1665702715216.html\" title=\"Window property that determines whether the user can minimize the form or application window at run time, and enables the Minimize/Restore button in the title bar.\">Iconize (CanIconize)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40400e1_d40401e1_d40402e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qkn1665702715286.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qkn1665702715286.html\" title=\"Determines whether the user can maximize and restore the size of the form or application window using the Maximize/Restore button in the title bar.\">Maximize</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40403e1_d40404e1_d40405e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ugr1665702834531.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ugr1665702834531.html\" title=\"Window property of a form component that determines whether the user can close the form window by clicking the Close button in the title bar.\">Close (CanClose) [FRM]</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40406e1_d40407e1_d40408e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kjr1676877187333.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kjr1676877187333.html\" title=\"Window property of a form or application shell that determines whether the window can be resized at runtime.\">Resizable (CanResize)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40409e1_d40410e1_d40411e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ygs1665702834602.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ygs1665702834602.html\" title=\"Window property that determines whether scrollbars are displayed on the form at runtime, if necessary. Valid values: True or False (default).\">No Form Scrollbars (NOFORMSCROLL)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40412e1_d40413e1_d40414e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"azm1665702712331.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azm1665702712331.html\" title=\"Window property of a form that specifies the reading orientation of the form at runtime. If set to right-to-left, the layout and text orientation are mirrored.\">Direction</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__ul_zbp_khl_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40415e1_d40416e1_d40417e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eao1665702652656.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eao1665702652656.html\" title=\"Window property that controls whether layout information is kept. Values are True (default) or False.\">Keep Layout State (KeepLayout)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40418e1_d40419e1_d40420e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oix1665702652724.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oix1665702652724.html\" title=\"Determines how the layout state for forms and grid widgets is stored. Valid values are PROCESS, COMPONENT, or INSTANCE.\">Layout State Storage (LAYOUTSTORAGE)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__ul_dcp_khl_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40421e1_d40422e1_d40423e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uia1665702644018.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uia1665702644018.html\" title=\"Type of image to use as a background or icon—Glyph or File.\">Image Type</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40424e1_d40425e1_d40426e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lsu1665702783988.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsu1665702783988.html\" title=\"Name of form instance that the current form will overlay. This ensures that the current form is only displayed over the specified parent, and disappears when focus is switches to another form instance. This property can only be set if the current form is a Contained Form or if the property Is Independent Form is false.\">Parent Form (TABPAGE)</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__section_lmw_lhl_swb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d292795e510\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__ul_e1v_mhl_swb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wfn1665703029011__li_d40451e1_d40452e1_d40453e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"euw1665702582150.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/euw1665702582150.html\" title=\"A Form is a stateful presentation Component that enables users to view and modify data in a Windows or character mode application.\">Form</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rld1665702581999.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Auto Close (AutoClose)</a><p>Window property of a form that determines what happens when it loses input focus. It may be automatically closed and the Quit or Accept trigger fired , or it may stay open and be explicitly closed. Valid values: Quit or True, Accept , or False.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hwg1665702769717.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Cell Height (CellHeight)</a><p>Window property that defines the size of the virtual grid used in the form layout, expressed as a percentage of Font0. The grid is used when defining the form dimensions and the size and position of objects in the form layout.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ugr1665702834531.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Close (CanClose) [FRM]</a><p>Window property of a form component that determines whether the user can close the form window by clicking the Close button in the title bar.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azm1665702712331.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Direction</a><p>Window property of a form that specifies the reading orientation of the form at runtime. If set to right-to-left, the layout and text orientation are mirrored.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oix1665702652724.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Layout State Storage (LAYOUTSTORAGE)</a><p>Determines how the layout state for forms and grid widgets is stored. Valid values are PROCESS, COMPONENT, or INSTANCE.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mbl1665702769794.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Line Space (LineSpace)</a><p>Runtime Window property of a Uniface form, which specifies the number of pixels between vertically adjacent fields.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ygs1665702834602.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>No Form Scrollbars (NOFORMSCROLL)</a><p>Window property that determines whether scrollbars are displayed on the form at runtime, if necessary. Valid values: True or False (default).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsu1665702783988.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Parent Form (TABPAGE)</a><p>Name of form instance that the current form will overlay. This ensures that the current form is only displayed over the specified parent, and disappears when focus is switches to another form instance. This property can only be set if the current form is a Contained Form or if the property Is Independent Form is false.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dto1665702580637.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Window Type (WindowType)</a><p>Window property of a form that determines the type of window used to display the form. One of: Normal | Dialog | Primary | Secondary | Contained | Popup</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616704\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616704\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Window Properties Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Window Properties This property defines an associative list of properties that control the appearance and behavior of a form component running in a Windows environment. Example: $windowproperties(\"FORM2\", \"backimage\") = \"backimage=@%%LOGO.MYENT%%%.png\") Expected Value: String Default Value: None Description The window properties are the widget properties of a form component. Selected properties can be set in ProcScript using newinstance and $windowproperties . For more information, see newinstance and $windowproperties . Window Properties The following window properties can be set declaratively in Window Properties , and dynamically with the $widgetproperties ProcScript function. Background Color (BackColor) Foreground Color (ForeColor) Background Image (BackImage) Horizontal Alignment (Halign) Vertical Alignment ( Valign) Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale) Vertical Scaling ( Vscale) Preserve Aspect Ratio ( PreserveAspect) The following window properties can be set declaratively in Window Properties , and in ProcScript with newinstance . Window Type (WindowType) Modality Auto Close (AutoClose) The following properties can be set declaratively in Window Properties , but not in ProcScript: Caption System Menu (SysMenu) Iconize (CanIconize) Maximize Close (CanClose) [FRM] Resizable (CanResize) No Form Scrollbars (NOFORMSCROLL) Direction Keep Layout State (KeepLayout) Layout State Storage (LAYOUTSTORAGE) Image Type Parent Form (TABPAGE) Applies To Form Related Links Auto Close (AutoClose) Window property of a form that determines what happens when it loses input focus. It may be automatically closed and the Quit or Accept trigger fired , or it may stay open and be explicitly closed. Valid values: Quit or True, Accept , or False. Cell Height (CellHeight) Window property that defines the size of the virtual grid used in the form layout, expressed as a percentage of Font0. The grid is used when defining the form dimensions and the size and position of objects in the form layout. Close (CanClose) [FRM] Window property of a form component that determines whether the user can close the form window by clicking the Close button in the title bar. Direction Window property of a form that specifies the reading orientation of the form at runtime. If set to right-to-left, the layout and text orientation are mirrored. Layout State Storage (LAYOUTSTORAGE) Determines how the layout state for forms and grid widgets is stored. Valid values are PROCESS, COMPONENT, or INSTANCE. Line Space (LineSpace) Runtime Window property of a Uniface form, which specifies the number of pixels between vertically adjacent fields. No Form Scrollbars (NOFORMSCROLL) Window property that determines whether scrollbars are displayed on the form at runtime, if necessary. Valid values: True or False (default). Parent Form (TABPAGE) Name of form instance that the current form will overlay. This ensures that the current form is only displayed over the specified parent, and disappears when focus is switches to another form instance. This property can only be set if the current form is a Contained Form or if the property Is Independent Form is false. Window Type (WindowType) Window property of a form that determines the type of window used to display the form. One of: Normal | Dialog | Primary | Secondary | Contained | Popup Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}